  <iprostep id="step0" points="1"><div><p>Find the interval in which the function <iproformula style="margin-bottom: -3px; vertical-align: middle;" type="text" src="geteq.ashx?eqtext= f(x)=@abs{x+~x\}"/> is increasing.</p><p>(Use symbolic notation and fractions where needed. Give your answer as interval in the form (*,*).)</p><p><iproelement_short id="@step.s@id" version="2" correct="(-~x\,&amp;inf;)" tolerance="0.0" type="math" format="" answerrule="any" points="" size="2" checksyntax="true" allowedwords="" elid="1"/></p><p><a href="http://ebooks.bfwpub.com/calculus2e.php?page=1_1" target="_blank"><img src="images/uploaded_2f89a34a8ab748c8881de97827d0f9f4_eBook1.jpg" alt="ebook_image" border="0"/></a></p></div>&#160;<p/><p/><input class="next" id="@step.next" onclick="javascript:next('next', '@step')" type="button" value="Continue" hide="no"/><ipronav navtype="correct" next="step0corr"/><ipronav navtype="incorrect" next="step0inc"/></iprostep>
